text.tspan: Monthly reported cases of severe acute respiratory infections
Severe acute respiratory illnesses are defined by the WHO as acute respiratory infections with history of fever
or measured fever of ≥ 38 C°, cough, with onset within the last 10 days, and which require hospitalization. This
can include diseases other than influenza, such as COVID-19.
Data source: FluID by the World Health Organization (2023)
